Q(m)
 Q(m)=\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}\prod_{i=1}^k\left(1-\frac{i}m\right). 
 Q(m)\leqslant\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}\mathrm e^{-k(k+1)/(2m)}\leqslant1+\sum_{k=1}^{m-1}\int_{k-1}^k\mathrm e^{-x^2/(2m)}\mathrm dx, 
 Q(m)\leqslant1+\int_{0}^{+\infty}\mathrm e^{-x^2/(2m)}\mathrm dx=1+\sqrt{\frac\pi2m}. 
 Q(m)\geqslant\sum_{k=0}^{m^{3/4}}\prod_{i=1}^k\left(1-\frac{i}m\right)\geqslant\sum_{k=0}^{m^{3/4}}\mathrm e^{-C_mk(k+1)/(2m)}, 
 \frac1{\sqrt{m}}Q(m)\geqslant\frac1{\sqrt{m}}\int_1^{m^{3/4}}\mathrm e^{-C_mx^2/(2m)}\mathrm dx=\frac1{\sqrt{C_m}}\int_{\sqrt{C_m/m}}^{m^{1/4}\sqrt{C_m}}\mathrm e^{-x^2/2}\mathrm dx. 
 \liminf\frac1{\sqrt{m}}Q(m)\geqslant\int_{0}^{+\infty}\mathrm e^{-x^2/2}\mathrm dx=\sqrt{\frac\pi2}. 
