Q_2(m)=Q(m)+\frac12Q'(m)
 Q'(m)=\frac1m\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}k(k+1)\prod_{i=1}^k\left(1-\frac{i}m\right). 
 Q'(m)\leqslant\frac1m\sum_{k=0}^{m-1}k(k+1)\mathrm e^{-k(k+1)/(2m)}\leqslant\frac1m\sum_{k=1}^{m-1}\int_{k-1}^k(x+2)^2\mathrm e^{-x^2/(2m)}\mathrm dx, 
 Q'(m)\leqslant\frac1m\int_{0}^{+\infty}(x+2)^2\mathrm e^{-x^2/(2m)}\mathrm dx=\sqrt{m}\int_{0}^{+\infty}\left(x+\frac2{\sqrt{m}}\right)^2\mathrm e^{-x^2/2}\mathrm dx, 
 Q'(m)\leqslant\sqrt{m}\int_{0}^{+\infty}\mathrm e^{-x^2/2}\mathrm dx+O(1)=\sqrt{\frac\pi2m}+O(1). 
 \lim\frac1{\sqrt{m}}Q'(m)=\sqrt{\frac\pi2}. 
